16:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. AIVA is best suited for film and game composers, orchestral and classical music, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Play.ht, meanwhile, shines for developers needing TTS API, podcast intros and voiceovers, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2016, AIVA describes itself as \"AI composer for emotional soundtracks and music.\" Play.ht, established in 2016, positions itself as \"Ultra-realistic AI voice generator and text-to-speech.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
17:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Play.ht** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (6 vs 1), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean AIVA is a poor choice — far from it. AIVA excels in its own right, particularly for film and game composers and orchestral and classical music.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value high-quality voices, go with Play.ht. If excellent orchestral compositions matters more to you, AIVA is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
